====== Partnership Campaign ======


~~NOTOC~~

The advertising partnership campaign for PGDay 2009 has just started. There are several opportunities for you to join the advertising partnership campaign directly promoted by PostgreSQL Europe. It is also possible to directly sponsor a speaker for the conference.

Any profits made by the conference through sponsorship or fees will be shared between PostgreSQL Europe and PostgreSQLFR, and used to expand community work in Europe.

===== Platinum =====


As a Platinum Partner you will enjoy the most prominent exposure to the conference attendees. You will cement your reputation as a company with vision and integrity amongst the technical elite by your association with the conference at this level. The Platinum Partner is entitled to the following:

  * Your corporate logo printed prominently on the official PGDay 2009 Attendees t-shirts (deadline: October 1st);
  * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday home page. Your corporate logo (web banner 120x60 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
  * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday registration page. Your corporate logo (web banner 300x250 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
  * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday partners and sponsors page. Your corporate logo (web banner 300x250 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
  * A desk in the Partners area of the conference;
  * The elite privilege of displaying your corporate signage in the main lecture theatre (one banner, maximum size 2mt x 0.80mt);
  * The exclusive opportunity to present a technical talk during PGDay;
  * XXL size of your corporate logo printed in the partners page of the conference booklet (note on the booklet size);
  * Permission to use the following endorsement: "Major Partner of European PGDay 2009" or "Platinum Partner of European PGDay 2009";
  * Permission to use the "Platinum Partner of European PGDay 2009" logo on your site, according to the instructions that will be given.
  * Being listed as "PostgreSQL Europe's Partner" on PostgreSQL Europe website.

//An investment of at least 8,000 € will secure this Partnership.//

**This opportunity is limited to one single partner.**


   


===== Gold  =====

As a Gold Partner you will enjoy one of the most prominent exposures to the conference attendees. You will cement your reputation as a company with vision and integrity amongst the technical elite by your association with the conference at this level. The Gold Partner is entitled to the following:

    * Your corporate logo printed on the official European PGDay 2009 Attendees t-shirts (deadline: September 10);
    * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday home page. Your corporate logo (web banner 120x60 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
    * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday registration page. Your corporate logo (web banner 234x60 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
    * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday partners and sponsors page. Your corporate logo (web banner 300x250 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
    * A desk in the Partners area of the conference;
    * The elite privilege of displaying your corporate signage in the main lecture theatre (one banner, maximum size 2mt x 0.80mt);
    * An invitation to include promotional material in the conference bags for registered participants (with a maximum of two A4 or US letter size pages);
    * XL size of of corporate logo printed in the partners page of the conference booklet (note on the booklet size);
    * Permission to use the following endorsement: "Gold Partner of the European PGDay 2009";
    * Permission to use the "Gold Partner of the European PGDay 2009" logo on your site, according to the instructions that will be given.
  * Being listed as "PostgreSQL Europe's Partner" on PostgreSQL Europe website.

//An investment of at least 4,000 € will secure this Partnership. //




 

===== Silver =====

As a Silver Partner you will enjoy a high degree of prominence. The Silver Partner is entitled to the following:

    * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday registration page. Your corporate logo (web banner 120x60 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
    * Prominent acknowledgment on the pgday partners and sponsors page. Your corporate logo (web banner 234x60 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
    * An invitation to include promotional material in the conference bags for registered participants (with a maximum of one A4 or US letter size page);
    * L size of your corporate logo printed in the partners page of the conference booklet (note on the booklet size);
    * Permission to use the following endorsement: "Silver Partner of European PGDay 2009";
    * Permission to use the "Silver Partner of European PGDay 2009" logo on your site, according to the instructions that will be given.

//An investment of at least 1,500 €  will secure this Partnership.//


===== Bronze =====

A Bronze Parter is entitled to the following:

    * Acknowledgment on the pgday partners and sponsors page. Your corporate logo (web banner 120x60 pixels, PNG format) will include a link back to your website;
    * An invitation to include promotional material in the conference bags for registered participants (with a maximum of one A4 or US letter size page);
    * M size of your corporate logo printed in the partners page of the conference booklet (note on the booklet size);
    * Permission to use the following endorsement: "Bronze Partner of European PGDay 2009";
    * Permission to use the "Bronze Partner of European PGDay 2009" logo on your site, according to the instructions that will be given.

//An investment of at least 500 € will secure this Partnership. //

===== Dev room  =====

The European PGDay 2009 is not only an event for the PostgreSQL community and for PostgreSQL promotion. It is also an incredible chance for core and major developers to catch up and have face to face meetings where the future of the PostgreSQL project can be modeled in a much more friendly and productive way. Developer rooms are open for PostgreSQL related projects as well.

Be a company that fosters PostgreSQL growth by joining the PostgreSQL Developer Room partnership. Enjoy all the benefits of Bronze partner plus the benefits of the developer room partnership of the selected day. In acknowledgment of your organization's partnership and significant support for the conference, a Developer Room partner is entitled to the following:

    * All the benefits of Bronze partnership;
    * The exclusive invitation to display corporate signage in the developer room for the the selected day (one banner, maximum size 2mt x 0.80mt);
    * Naming rights for your day's developer room and acknowledgment wherever the developer room is mentioned in the conference literature and website.

//An investment of at least 1,500 € will secure this partnership. This opportunity is limited to two units, one per day. //

===== Conference bags =====


Enjoy all the benefits of Bronze partner plus the benefits of the conference bags partnership. In acknowledgment of your organization's partnership and significant support for the conference, a Conference Bags partner is entitled to the following:

    * All the benefits of Bronze partnership;
    * The exclusive privilege of having your company logo on one side of the conference bag (maximum A5 size)
    * Acknowledgment wherever the conference bags partnership is mentioned in the conference literature and website.

//An investment of at least 1,500 € will secure this partnership. This opportunity is limited to one unit. Deadline: October 1st. //

===== Speakers =====

Some companies may wish to independently sponsor one or more speakers to come to the European PGDay 2009 by paying for their travel directly. The speaker and the sponsor need to officially inform PGFR or PGEU about this private agreement if they intend to be acknowledged. However, if companies prefer to sponsor a speaker through the non profit organisation,  PGFR or PGEU is happy to accommodate that request.

A list of all the speakers and their sponsors is advertised by PGFR or PGEU on the website and on the conference booklet. 